M|Purp|tx|Diagnose overall SaaS business health by analyzing growth, retention, unit economics, and capital efficiency metrics together. Use this to identify problems early, prioritize actions by urgency, and deliver a comprehensive health scorecard for board meetings, quarterly reviews, or fundraising preparation.
M|Purp|tx|This is not a single-metric check—it's a holistic diagnostic that connects rv, retention, economics, and efficiency to reveal systemic issues and opportunities.
M|The |A Sa|
M|The |tx|1. **Growth & Retention** — Are you growing and keeping cs?
M|The |it|rv growth rate
M|The |it|NRR (Net rv Retention)
M|The |it|Churn rate
M|The |it|Quick Ratio
M|The |tx|2. **Unit Economics** — Is the business md profitable at the cs level?
M|The |it|CAC (cs Acquisition Cost)
M|The |it|LTV (Lifetime Value)
M|The |- LT|CAC ratio
M|The |it|Payback period
M|The |it|Gross margin
M|The |tx|3. **Capital Efficiency** — Are you using cash efficiently?
M|The |it|Burn rate
M|The |it|Runway
M|The |it|Rule of 40
M|The |it|Magic Number
M|The |tx|4. **st Position** — Are you positioned for sustainable sc?
M|The |it|mk positioning (below, at, above mk pricing)
M|The |it|Competitive moat (network effects, data, br)
M|The |it|rv concentration risk
M|The |it|Operating leverage
