M|Stag|- Pr|>10%
M|Stag|- Re|Positive or near-positive cash flow
M|Red |**Cr|**
M|Red |it|Runway <6 months
M|Red |- LT|CAC <1.5:1
M|Red |it|Churn accelerating cohort-over-cohort
M|Red |it|NRR <90%
M|Red |it|Magic Number <0.3
M|Red |**Hi|**
M|Red |it|Rule of 40 <25
M|Red |it|Payback >24 months
M|Red |it|Quick Ratio <2
M|Red |it|Gross margin <60%
M|Red |it|rv concentration >50% in top 10 cs
M|Red |**Me|**
M|Red |it|NRR 90-100% (flat, not growing)
M|Red |it|Magic Number 0.3-0.5
M|Red |it|Operating leverage negative
M|Red |it|Churn rate stable but hi (>5% monthly)
M|Anti|- **|** "rv is growing 50%, we're great!" (ignoring burn, churn, unit economics)
M|Anti|- **|** Early-stage burn is acceptable; scale-stage burn is a problem
M|Anti|- **|** Health is directional—are metrics improving or degrading?
M|Anti|- **|** Context matters (competitive pressure, mk changes, team capacity)
M|When|**Us|**
M|When|it|Preparing for board meetings or investor updates
M|When|it|Quarterly business reviews (QBR)
M|When|it|Fundraising preparation (know your numbers)
M|When|it|Annual planning (identify improvement areas)
M|When|it|You suspect problems but can't pinpoint them
M|When|it|New PM/exec joining and needs health assessment
M|When|**Do|**
M|When|it|You're pre-rv (focus on pd-mk fit first)
M|When|it|You're in pure research mode (not enough data)
M|When|- Yo|feature, channel, pricing)
